1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:07,000
Every physics student has done this:
memorize a formula, plug in numbers...

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:12,760
...and get an answer you don't actually understand.

3
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:18,860
Real labs are expensive — most of us never touch one.

4
00:00:18,860 --> 00:00:26,240
So we built a physics lab that lives in your browser.
Axiom Studio — physics you can actually touch.

5
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:31,720
Any browser becomes a real physics lab.
No account, no setup — just open it.

6
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:42,920
Under the hood: real physics engines,
RK4 integration, true orbital mechanics.

7
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:45,000
Not fake animations — the real deal.

8
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:50,500
Here's what makes it different. Every experiment
follows three steps. First: predict.

9
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:57,000
Before anything runs, I commit to an answer.
Will this projectile land here, or here?

10
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Then: experiment. Adjust the parameters —
angle, velocity — and run the real simulation.

11
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:16,500
And finally: understand.
Meet Axion, our AI tutor.

12
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:31,440
It doesn't give a generic textbook answer — it reads
your numbers and prediction, and explains exactly why.

13
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:33,640
Projectile motion is just the start.

14
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:39,560
Pendulum dynamics for harmonic motion.
Collision physics for conservation laws.

15
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:46,000
And my favorite — orbital mechanics, in full 3D.

16
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Same loop every time: predict, experiment, understand.

17
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:59,000
That's how real intuition gets built — accessible
to anyone with a browser.

18
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:04,000
For free. Built for DHS Hacks — live now at
axiom-studio20.vercel.app.

19
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Thanks for watching.
